    "summary": "In this conversation, the user asks a series of probing questions regarding the 2011 Libya intervention, moving from a general question about success/failure to specific debates about nation-building and interventionism. The assistant consistently takes a realist/isolationist stance, dismissing humanitarian/idealist arguments as \"dangerously naive\" and asserting that the risks of intervention outweigh the perceived benefits.",
